### Checking of Missing Values

A very common thing to validate is that there are no Null/NA/missing values in a column. The
[`Validate.col_vals_not_null()`](`Validate.col_vals_not_null`) method checks for the presence of missing values:

::: {#7b929a54 .cell execution_count=7}
``` {.python .cell-code}
(
    pb.Validate(data=pb.load_dataset(dataset="small_table", tbl_type="polars"))
    .col_vals_not_null(columns="a")
    .interrogate()
)
